ill `cancelOrder` work? After `createOrder`, line 56 does `repo.update(id, { status: 'confirmed', total: payment.amount })`. With the fix (spreading existing), the stored order will have all fields including `items`. Then `cancelOrder` calls `repo.findById(id)` which copies. Good.\n\nBut there's another subtle issue: the event emitted by `cancelOrder` does NOT include `status: 'cancelled'`, but the `InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled` checks for `status: 'cancelled'` at line 50. The direct inventory test (inventory.test.ts:73-79) passes `status: 'cancelled'` explicitly, but when going through `OrderService.cancelOrder`, it's not included.\n\nLet me fix all bugs now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1759,"cache_read_input_tokens":35497,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1759},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"11532515-baa0-445b-ba7b-df46ffd86417","uuid":"ad1107bd-5110-4b6d-adfc-3adcb18087a9"}
